HEADWORD: Sea urchin
<hw>Sea" ur"chin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
numerous species of echinoderms of the order
<ord>Echinoidea</ord>.</def> <note>When living they are covered with
movable spines which are often long and sharp.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seave</ent>⟦br⟧
